column2: Variable Label
column3: Response Labels (Note that 999 includes not asked, not applicable, refused, no response)

column2: Wave
Waves 1 & 1.5 Combined
Unique Case Identification across All Waves
column3: [numeric]
column15: This variable was created when the wave files were merged. It has no inherent meaning, and simply provides a way of uniquely identifying individual cases.

column2: Case Identification within Wave
column3: [numeric]
column15: These IDs were assigned at the time of survey completion. They are unique within wave, but not across all waves.

column2: Final Post Stratification Weights
column3: [numeric]
column15: These weights were produced by the panel companies for each individual wave and are centred around the number of respondents requested. This is not always the number of cases in the wave, so the total N for the merged file may be different from the number of cases once weighting is applied.
